ownedComment.body: Author:ZOO. Created:6/21/05 9:04 AM. Title:. Comment:.
Represents the style of the web service.

Represents a web service, this is usually used in combination with the <<Service>> stereotype because of the fact the service stereotype indicates a service implementation (like Spring, or Session EJBs must be generated). However, WebService can be standalone without an EJB implementation.
Denotes the use of the web service: can be 'literal' or 'encoded'. Default=literal.
Denotes the provider for the web service: can be 'EJB' or 'RPC' or 'JAX-WS'. Default=default. Not applicable for JAX-WS.
The style of the web service, can be 'rpc', 'document', or 'wrapped''. Default=document.

Validate incoming/outgoing XML against the declared schema. Default=false allows minor service revisions to use the same service version when optional attributes are added to the new minor revision. JAX-WS and CXF services only - sets options in Spring ApplicationContext.xml.
Overrides the global wsdlSoapAddress setting for this WebService class.
If Jaxb2 SimpleBindingMode should be used when generating Java objects from the WSDL web service definition using the wsdl2java utility. Default=true.

Override global default XJC arguments used when creating Jaxb XML bindings from the webservice definition through the wsdl2java utility. Default is -Xcommons-lang,-Xcommons-lang:ToStringStyle=DEFAULT_STYLE,-Xdefault-value,-Xvalue-constructor,-Xcollection-setter-injector,-simple-preserve. This creates toString method using apache commons-lang, creates ValueObject constructor, get/set on Collection types, and allows preserving methods and some code across multiple code generation invocations.
serialVersionUID to be applied to the WebService class.
Implement this class as a CXF REST webservice. This is the only value required to be set, all the other REST options are set to default values unless overridden.
Adds @Context annotations to the service. Context(s) are comma or semicolon or pipe delimited, appear on separate lines within the Service class.
URL path for REST webservice. default=lowercase class name.
REST Request type (GET, POST, etc).
Type of service output procuced by the service.
Media type consumed by this service.
Marks service with @Provider annotation, used with @Produces and @Consumes
ElementType. default=METHOD.
RetentionPolicy. default=RUNTIME.
Custom Http Method, something other than GET/PUT/POST.
Log incoming and outgoing XML messages in CXF. Configures Spring logging. default=true, but the Spring Cofiguration is not overwritten if changed.
Additional annotations should be separated by semi colons. The annotations should be fully qualified.
Additional annotations should be separated by semi colons. The annotations should be fully qualified.
Additional annotations should be separated by semi colons. The annotations should be fully qualified.

Indicates a web service operation: this allows us to expose only certain operations on a given <<Service>> whereas the <<WebService>> stereotype exposed service and all its operations as a webservice.
For example, a service sometimes may contain other operations that will not be exposed externally as a web service, if an operation is stereotyped with this, then only those operations will be exposed.
Overrides defaultParameterStyle setting for this WebServiceOperation.
URL path for REST webservice. default=/parameter/{parameter}/ for each parameter, appended in parameter order.
REST Request type (GET, POST, etc).

Sets cache-control headers on a successful GET request for the operation. @Cache @NoCache and CacheControl annotations supported. @Cache adds the String values to the annotation, NoCache creates the @NoCache annotation.
Adds @Encoded annotation. default=false (no annotation)
Adds @Produces annotation with the Media Type produced
Adds @Consumes annotation with the Media Type consumed.
Adds @Provider annotation for customized provider implementation.
Multipart response part type annotation.
Annotates method with @Suspend(interval in ms), used for asynchronous responses and polling. default=0 (do not suspend, do not add annotation).
Comma separated list of security roles. May include 'all', 'none'.
Additional annotations should be separated by semi colons. The annotations should be fully qualified.
Represents the provider of the web service.
Represents the use of the web service.

Designates an Exception class as a JAX-WS WebFault, which creates a faultBean class referenced by the service containing a fault exception and cause in the same package as the Service, plus the original WebFault exception class annotated with @WebFault.
Defines if parameter style overrides the global defaultParameterStyle.
Http Request Type used in REST services. Default=GET if unspecified.
Parameter Type for REST webservice parameter. default=PathParam.
Additional Detail on WebService parameter, different than defaults.
Override the default webservice parameter name. default = parameter name. puts REST @PathParam annotation on service parameter, to customize the URL or parameter name created.
URL path for the service parameter, to be appended to the service operation path.
Adds @Encoded annotation to the parameter.
@PathParam annotation on service parameter, to customize the URL or parameter name created. default=parameter name (no annotation).
REST Parameter Types (PathParam, QueryParam, HeaderParam, MatrixParam, CookieParam, FormParam). default=PathParam.
URI fragment invoked on javax.ws.rs.core.PathSegment.
Additional annotations should be separated by semi colons. The annotations should be fully qualified.

On CXF/JAX-WS WebService or Operation, indicates that SOAP ws-security and transport security is enabled. It adds ws-security namespace and SOAP Header information to the service definition and WebService client.
Namespace abbreviation associated with the wssecurity element references.
Namespace associated with the custom header element references.
XSD Schema location associated with the wssecurity element references.
wsdl:part name associated with the wssecurity element references.
wsdl element name used in the wssecurity element references. Default=Security.
wsdl element document use type lieral/encoded. Default=literal.
The security type used in the webservice operation.

On CXF/JAX-WS WebService or Operation, indicates an additional custom SOAP header is enabled. It adds the header namespace and SOAP Header information to the service definition and WebService client. You must specify values for abbr, namespace, XSDLocation, partName, and element.
